Those planning secret New Year's Eve parties tonight should think twice. Authorities have beefed up their numbers, to make sure people obey the lockdown restrictions. eNCA reporter, Barry Bateman has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Those planning secret New Year's Eve parties on Thursday night should think twice. Authorities have beefed up their numbers to make sure people obey the lockdown restrictions. READ: SA Lockdown: Police clamp down on non-compliance in Joburg There are roadblocks across Gauteng. Police in the capital are looking for alcohol being transported illegally, drunken driving, and that public transport is not more than 70-percent full.